<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Speaker A · exact canon excerpt</p>
  <h2>Article One</h2>
  <blockquote class="reading"><p>From each as they will to each as they've given so all¹ may eat save those refusing to contribute to their comfort and safety² or whose actions destroy the comfort and safety³ of another.</p></blockquote>
  <div class="grid">
    <article class="panel"><h3>Plain orientation</h3><p>Article One begins with food because survival comes before ideology. It asks each person to give according to will and history of contribution, while naming refusal and harm as real constraints.</p></article>
    <article class="panel"><h3>Central tension</h3><p>The article must not become forced labor, moralized poverty, or blank entitlement. Its tension is provision without erasure: everyone eats, but the system still distinguishes need, contribution, refusal, and harm.</p></article>
  </div>
</section>
