  <article class="panel turn note"><span class="status status-interpretation">note ¹ · all</span><p><strong>Canon note:</strong> A cry sharpens vigilance. Fragility elicits innovation. Presence energizes dynamics. Dependency clarifies need. Burden highlights character.</p><p><strong>Function:</strong> prevents the vulnerable from being treated as waste. Need is not only a cost; it can reveal what the community has failed to perceive.</p></article>
  <article class="panel turn note"><span class="status status-interpretation">note ² · safety</span><p><strong>Canon note:</strong> safety exists only by skill, will, vigilance, and luck</p><p><strong>Function:</strong> rejects sentimental safety. Comfort and safety require competence, attention, choice, and humility before uncertainty.</p></article>
  <article class="panel turn note"><span class="status status-interpretation">note ³ · destructive action</span><p><strong>Canon note:</strong> The paper tiger. Malingering professionals. Greek gifts. Thieves. Red herrings. Narcissists. Empty calories. Liars. Celibate priests.</p><p><strong>Function:</strong> names false help, false authority, distraction, predation, and hollow provision as hazards to survival work.</p></article>
